<subSubSection id="C358655E86006B26FEC586BFFA4DF99A" pageId="18" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FEC586BFFB5FF3F8" blockId="18.[236,1223,2763,3171]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">Description. Shell very small, medium-spired turbiniform, coeloconoid, narrowly phaneromphalous. Protoconch of 11,4 smooth whorls, and a rather flat apex. Teleoconch whorl profile gently arched between sutures, rounded on the final whorl, sutures moderately deep, spiral lirae rising gradually on the second whorl, then becoming gradually stronger; 18 lirae between sutures, shell consisting of two layers. Aperture with straight inner lip thickened, slightly reflexed; outer lip orthocline.</paragraph>
