<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FAE68F27F8E4FC33" blockId="18.[1291,2275,621,1537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">Stratigraphic position. In bioclastic limestone, upper part of the Dangarfield Formation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FAE68FC4F96AFBA8" blockId="18.[1291,2275,621,1537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">
Additional material. 
<specimenCount id="9D44FD5C86006B26F9678FC4F80AFC4C" box="[1727,1936,944,983]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81" type="generic">6 specimens</specimenCount>
from south-east of 'Rangari' (Locality 18), and 10 from various horizons at Glenbawn (Locality 31).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FAE6884EF720FBFA" blockId="18.[1291,2275,621,1537]" box="[1342,2234,1082,1121]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">Geographic distribution. 'Rangari' to Glenbawn.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FAE6881CF7C0FB14" blockId="18.[1291,2275,621,1537]" box="[1342,2138,1128,1167]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">Geological age. Middle to late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FAE588E3F7B6FB77" blockId="18.[1291,2275,621,1537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">
Etymology. Derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B936EAC786006B26F86F88E3F7DBFB25" box="[1975,2113,1175,1214]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">turgidus</emphasis>
meaning swollen, referring to the inflated last whorl.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FAE58887FA4DF99A" blockId="18.[1291,2275,621,1537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686006B26FA228887F83AFA81" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1530,1952,1267,1306]" class="Gastropoda" family="Araeonematidae" genus="Rhabdotocochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="18" pageNumber="81" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turgida" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786006B26FA228887F83AFA81" box="[1530,1952,1267,1306]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">Rhabdotocochlis turgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC86006B26F86A8887F865FA81" box="[1970,2047,1267,1306]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686006B26FAD38955F94FFAD3" box="[1291,1749,1313,1352]" class="Gastropoda" family="Euomphalidae" genus="Araeonema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euomphalina" pageId="18" pageNumber="81" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="microspirulata">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786006B26FAD38955F94FFAD3" box="[1291,1749,1313,1352]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">Araeonema microspirulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a larger and thicker shell consisting of two layers, and coarser spiral lirae, and from the 
<typeStatus id="54F9887786006B26F9F68908F9EEFA3F" box="[1582,1652,1404,1444]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686006B26F8EE8908FA1FFA48" authority="Knight" authorityName="Knight" authorityYear="1933" class="Gastropoda" family="Araeonematidae" genus="Rhabdotocochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="18" pageNumber="81" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rugata">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786006B26F8EE8908F77BFA3F" box="[1846,2273,1404,1444]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">Rhabdotocochlis rugata</emphasis>
Knight
</taxonomicName>
, in having the more inflated last whorl and finer spiral lirae.
</paragraph>
